snippet.title: The vice-presidential debate between Kamala Harris and Mike Pence - 10/7 (FULL LIVE STREAM)
snippet.description:
Vice President Pence and Democratic vice-presidential nominee Kamala Harris will meet onstage at the University of Utah in Salt Lake City on Oct. 7. Susan Page, the Washington bureau chief at USA Today, will moderate. 

Public health experts have expressed concern at the decision by both presidential campaigns and the debate commission to move ahead with in-person events less than a week after President Trump tested positive for the novel coronavirus. The first presidential debate resulted in at least 11 positive cases by people involved in preparations.

The Post’s Libby Casey will anchor live, uninterrupted coverage and she will be joined by reporters Joyce Koh, Rhonda Colvin, James Hohmann, Hannah Jewell, Robert Costa, Amber Phillips, Jeremy Bowers, Philip Bump and Eugene Scott for analysis before and after the debate. Read more: https://wapo.st/3lgwB2K. Subscribe to The Washington Post on YouTube: https://wapo.st/2QOdcqK
